One dead in Kenya government building blast . One person was killed in an explosion at a government building in Nairobi on Sunday morning , Kenyan radio said . The blast , at the Bureau of Statistics in central Nairobi , happened at about 0400 local time , ( 0100 GMT ) , the radio said . Police said the incident was under investigation and the cause of the explosion was not immediately known . It caused only slight damage to one room , they said . The Bureau , which collects and publishes statistics on the economy and other subjects , closes over the weekend , and only a small security staff is on duty when it is closed , police said . The Bureau adjoins the headquarters of the Kenya Finance Ministry and the Central Bank of Kenya . It is only a few yards away from the Kenya Police headquarters . 
